ewal metrics today are tracked manually by the sourcing team (Discovery, 25 Feb 2026). No cost, cycle-time, or ROI figure was ever stated by the buyer on any call read; quantifying the migration/renewal savings case remains the open move."}, "champion": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Next Step 26 May 2026", "Next Step 9 Jun 2026", "Avoma POC Framework Review 28 Apr 2026"], "narrative": "Peter Hughes is the closest thing to a champion: he is named the internal 'CLM project lead' (Next Step, 26 May 2026), coordinated every workshop and scheduling decision from January through April, and was the sole recipient of the 9 Jun 2026 Zycus rep-transition note, making him the primary conduit into the buying committee. However, no call shows him explicitly advocating for Zycus internally or pushing back on Ironclad; his role reads as neutral process-owner rather than active promoter, and there has been no direct contact evidenced since the transition note. This is 'developing, at risk': developed = sole steady point of contact and internal project ownership; missing = demonstrated internal advocacy and any contact since early June."}, "competition": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Avoma Intro Call 23 Jan 2026", "Next Step 9 Jun 2026"], "narrative": "Cadence's legal team stated on the very first call that it was 'impressed by tools like iClad ' and has pressing AI requirements (Devesh Chadha, Intro Call, 23 Jan 2026) \u2014 a preference never directly countered since. Coupa is the incumbent CLM tool being displaced ('Currently using Coupa for CLM, seeking one platform...', 23 Jan 2026), and two low-cost intake tools ('Tonkin' and 'Yep') were evaluated and rejected for insufficient capability relative to cost (23 Jan 2026). As of 9 Jun 2026, Cadence is 'down to 1 of 2 vendors including Ironclad' \u2014 Zycus is a live finalist, but the legal constituency's early-stated preference for the rival is the wedge Ironclad still holds."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "confirmed"